{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"ANC1: Consistently below expectations in 2025, averaging ~64,200 vs. ~71,100 expected (~10% lower). July 2025 was ~66,300 (~10% lower).

ANC4: Stayed close to expected, averaging ~21,700 vs. ~22,400 expected (~3% lower). July 2025 was ~22,100 (~5% lower).

 ANC1 shows persistent shortfalls, and fewer women continue to ANC4, underscoring a continuity gap in antenatal care. Overall, both indicators align closely with expectations, but ANC1 shows a higher persistent shortfall compared to expected service use."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"f13bc674-ef5d-4619-9723-9bf804e56ee5","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Antenatal Care Service Use Similar to Expected Trends"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"BCG: Multiple sustained disruptions through 2023–2025, with service use ~10–24% below expected levels during shaded periods. After accounting for reporting completeness, the disruption in 2025 stands out as a real service decline.

Penta1: Brief disruptions in 2023 and 2024 with dips of ~5–14% below expected levels. Periods of disruptions were also observed in 2025, averaging ~12% below expected values. 

Penta3: Brief dips of ~5–13% below expected levels in 2023 and mid-2024, followed by small disruptions in early 2025, averaging ~6% below expected values."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.8,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"2f0728ba-d567-4d05-a8cb-936d32056d5a","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"BCG showed sustained disruptions through 2025; Penta disruptions were brief and primarily concentrated in 2025"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"ANC1 showed disruptions in mid-2025, averaging ~63,900 visits per month vs. ~70,400 expected (~9% lower), with ~62,900 visits in June 2025 (~11% lower than expected). 

ANC4 largely tracked expected trends throughout the period, without notable disruptions.

Far fewer women progress from ANC1 to ANC4, underscoring a persistent continuity gap in antenatal care."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"f13bc674-ef5d-4619-9723-9bf804e56ee5","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"ANC service shows disruption in 2025; ANC4 stays near trend, but continuity gap remains"}}
